commits.message: APIView - Visualize when assemblies expose internals via InternalsVisibleTo (#7116)

pull_request.title: APIView - Visualize when assemblies expose internals via InternalsVisibleTo
pull_request.body:
This change allows APIView to display when a client library exposes its internals to other assemblies (excluding Moq, `.Tests`, and `.Perf`) as well as any types that are designated as exposed via decoration with a `FriendAttribute`.

The following is what a diff looks like for `Azure.Identity`, which exposes internals to `Azure.Identity.BrokeredAuthentication`

![image](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-tools/assets/1279263/b7d62a86-874a-413b-b61d-254467e5fefd)

The following shows that the internals consumers can be commented:
![image](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-tools/assets/1279263/e2c153ab-09c0-4c19-b0f2-0ad362991e4d)

related #7086

issue.title: Previously created release plans are not showing the new SDK release milestone app
issue.body:
The Azure Workloads as a Platform team is preparing to release SDKs to complete exception work for Public Preview.  This is the release plan they were using but it does not have the SDK release milestone app.  Can engineering resolve?  Or does the service team need to have the old release plan marked as abandoned and then create a new release plan?   

Link to release plan - https://aka.ms/sdk-release-planner?release-plan-id=663a6257-074c-ee11-be6e-000d3a3418aa

comment.body:
> > We are getting lots of teams coming our way because of Ignite in November. Teams are working to get signoffs done before end of October.
> 
> If they are just coming then they should be fine. This is only needed for teams that had previous Release Plans.
> 
> > Let me know how long that would take and how complicated it will be
> 
> @praveenkuttappan was suggesting to add a button at the end of the API Readiness app (in the complete view) to generate the SDK milestone. This button will only be valid for teams that are not Private preview and that not have SDK milestone already created.
> 
> @ladonnaq what do you think?

Isn't there anyway to just do this for the service teams?  Meaning just add the milestone to existing release plans.

feat(analyzer): add rules regarding model name suffixes (#6916)

- add four rules checking the suffixes of model names
- upgrade Roslyn to `4.4.0.0` since new rules require some API
- fix and suppress warnings due to upgrade of Roslyn
- temporarily suppress AD0001
- minor refactoring of existing codes
- add test cases for the new rules

resolve #6905
